  "response": "For students interested in economics at the International Baccalaureate (IB) level, here are recommended subject choices:\n\nHigher Level (HL) Recommendations:\n1. Mathematics (Either Analysis or Applications)\n2. Economics\n3. Business Management or a Social Science\n\nStandard Level (SL) Recommendations:\n1. English or native language\n2. A science subject (like Business, Psychology, or Computer Science)\n3. A second language\n\nAdditional considerations:\n- Strong math skills are crucial for economics\n- Mathematics HL is preferred by top universities\n- Business Management complements economics well\n- Choose subjects you enjoy and are good at\n- Consider university entry requirements\n\nAdvice:\n- Check specific university requirements\n- Balance your subject choices\n- Consider your strengths and interests\n- Maintain a good overall balance of subjects\n\nFactors to consider:\n- Your academic strengths\n- Future university and career goals\n- Personal interest in subjects\n- Potential university prerequisites\n\nRemember that subject selection is personal and should align with your individual goals and abilities.\n\nWould you like more specific advice about your particular situation?",
